{"id":690,"parent_id":680,"book_id":1,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":690,"title":"Ecclesiastes 10","subtitle":"","short_title":"Eccl.","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 10"],[".studySummary",["i","A little folly destroys the reputation of the wise and honorable—The words of a wise man’s mouth are gracious—A fool is full of words."]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.1","order":"02.22.010.44648"},["b","1"],"Dead flies cause the ointment of the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"apothecary"],"to send forth a stinking savour:",["i","so doth"],"a little",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_1b"},"folly"],"him that is in reputation for wisdom",["i","and"],"honour."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.2","order":"02.22.010.44649"},["b","2"],"A wise man’s heart",["i","is"],"at his right hand; but a fool’s heart at his left."],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.3","order":"02.22.010.44650"},["b","3"],"Yea also, when he that is a fool walketh by the way, his wisdom faileth",["i","him,"],"and he saith to every one",["i","that"],"he",["i","is"],"a fool."],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.4","order":"02.22.010.44651"},["b","4"],"If the spirit of the ruler rise up against thee, leave not thy place; for yielding pacifieth great offences."],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.5","order":"02.22.010.44652"},["b","5"],"There is an evil",["i","which"],"I have seen under the sun, as an error",["i","which"],"proceedeth from the ruler:"],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.6","order":"02.22.010.44653"},["b","6"],"Folly is set in great dignity, and the rich sit in low place."],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.7","order":"02.22.010.44654"},["b","7"],"I have seen",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_7a"},"servants"],"upon horses, and princes walking as servants upon the earth."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.8","order":"02.22.010.44655"},["b","8"],"He that diggeth a pit shall",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_8a"},"fall"],"into it; and whoso breaketh an hedge, a serpent shall bite him."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.9","order":"02.22.010.44656"},["b","9"],"Whoso removeth stones shall be hurt therewith;",["i","and"],"he that cleaveth wood shall be endangered thereby."],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.10","order":"02.22.010.44657"},["b","10"],"If the iron be blunt, and he do not whet the edge, then must he put to more strength: but wisdom",["i","is"],"profitable to direct."],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.11","order":"02.22.010.44658"},["b","11"],"Surely the serpent will bite without enchantment; and a babbler is no better."],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.12","order":"02.22.010.44659"},["b","12"],"The",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_12a"},"words"],"of a wise man’s mouth",["i","are"],"gracious; but the lips of a",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_12b"},"fool"],"will swallow up himself."],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.13","order":"02.22.010.44660"},["b","13"],"The beginning of the words of his mouth",["i","is"],"foolishness: and the end of his talk",["i","is"],"mischievous",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_13a"},"madness"],"."],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.14","order":"02.22.010.44661"},["b","14"],"A fool also is full of words: a man cannot tell what shall be; and what shall be after him, who can tell him?"],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.15","order":"02.22.010.44662"},["b","15"],"The labour of the foolish wearieth every one of them, because he knoweth not how to go to the city."],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.16","order":"02.22.010.44663"},["b","16"],"¶Woe to thee, O land, when thy king",["i","is"],"a",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_16a"},"child"],", and thy princes eat in the morning!"],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.17","order":"02.22.010.44664"},["b","17"],"Blessed",["i","art"],"thou, O land, when thy king",["i","is"],"the son of nobles, and thy princes eat in due season, for strength, and not for",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_17a"},"drunkenness"],"!"],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.18","order":"02.22.010.44665"},["b","18"],"¶By much",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_18a"},"slothfulness"],"the building decayeth; and through",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_18b"},"idleness"],"of the hands the house droppeth through."],["div",{"id":"19","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.19","order":"02.22.010.44666"},["b","19"],"¶A feast is made for laughter, and wine maketh merry: but money answereth all",["i","things."]],["div",{"id":"20","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.20","order":"02.22.010.44667"},["b","20"],"¶Curse not the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_20a"},"king"],", no not in thy thought; and curse not the rich in thy bedchamber: for a bird of the air shall carry the voice, and that which hath wings shall tell the matter."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.1a","order":"02.22.010.44668"},["b","1a"],["span.small","OR"],"perfumer (ointment maker)."],["div",{"id":"1b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.1b","order":"02.22.010.44670"},["b","1b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/7.11.1,11-12"},"Josh. 7:11 (1, 11–12)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/9.18"},"Eccl. 9:18"],"."],["div",{"id":"7a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.7a","order":"02.22.010.44672"},["b","7a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/prov/19.10"},"Prov. 19:10"],"."],["div",{"id":"8a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.8a","order":"02.22.010.44674"},["b","8a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/30.60"},"Alma 30:60"],"."],["div",{"id":"12a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.12a","order":"02.22.010.44676"},["b","12a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/prov/10.32"},"Prov. 10:32"],"."],["div",{"id":"12b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.12b","order":"02.22.010.44678"},["b","12b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/9.28.28-29"},"2 Ne. 9:28 (28–29)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/19.17"},"19:17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/35.7"},"D&C 35:7"],"."],["div",{"id":"13a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.13a","order":"02.22.010.44680"},["b","13a"],["span.small","IE"],"extreme folly."],["div",{"id":"16a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.16a","order":"02.22.010.44682"},["b","16a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/3.4.4-5,12"},"Isa. 3:4 (4–5, 12)"],"."],["div",{"id":"17a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.17a","order":"02.22.010.44684"},["b","17a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/word-of-wisdom"},"TG Word of Wisdom"],"."],["div",{"id":"18a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.18a","order":"02.22.010.44686"},["b","18a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/laziness"},"TG Laziness"],"."],["div",{"id":"18b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.18b","order":"02.22.010.44688"},["b","18b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/idleness"},"TG Idleness"],"."],["div",{"id":"20a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/eccl/10.20a","order":"02.22.010.44690"},["b","20a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/citizenship"},"TG Citizenship"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/kings-earthly"},"Kings, Earthly"],"."]]}
